2.4Scope of services
The scope of this assignment covers the design, development, deployment, and support of a
centralized Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system that is tailored to KASNEB’s
stakeholder engagement and service delivery needs.
The selected vendor will be expected to undertake the following:
1. System Design and Functional Requirements
• Conduct a detailed system analysis and design based on KASNEB’s stakeholder-service
mapping and institutional workflows.
• Translate the mapped services into CRM modules including, but not limited to:
i. Case management (enquiries, requests, complaints)
ii. Stakeholder profiles and engagement history
iii. Role-based access and approvals
iv. SLA monitoring and escalation mechanisms
v. Communication tracking (email, phone, social media, portal queries)
vi. Reports and dashboards
vii. Sales management (leads, opportunities, proposals, pipeline tracking)
viii. Marketing automation (campaigns, email marketing, social media integration)
ix. Customer retention and loyalty management (feedback, satisfaction surveys, churn
prediction)
x. Collaboration tools (internal notes, team activity tracking, approval workflows)
2. System Development and Customization
● Develop or configure the CRM system to meet KASNEB’s business requirements.
● Ensure system responsiveness, user-friendly interface, and mobile accessibility.
● Incorporate configurable workflows, service categories, and resolution timelines.
3. Integration with Existing Systems
● Integrate the CRM with KASNEB’s ERP (Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central) to
enable visibility of student and financial information.
● Integrate with other existing systems and portals such as:
o Student portal
o Accreditation portal
o Contact centre system
o Gmail (for email tracking)
o Social media platforms (as applicable)
o SMS Gateway
o ESS Portal
o Markers’ Portal
o Setters’ Portal
o Employers’ Portal
o MyLOFT

4. Security, Access Control, and Compliance
● Implement role-based access control with proper authentication protocols.
● Ensure compliance with the Data Protection Act and internal information security
standards.
● Include comprehensive audit logging of user actions.
5. Testing and Quality Assurance
● Conduct unit, system, and user acceptance testing (UAT) in collaboration with KASNEB’s
ICT and user departments.
● Facilitate bug fixing and performance tuning based on test outcomes.
6. Training and Knowledge Transfer
● Provide detailed training for system administrators, end users, and supervisors across
relevant directorates.
● Deliver user manuals and system documentation.
7. Deployment and Go-Live Support
● Deploy the CRM system in a secure production environment.
● Provide on-site support during go-live and stabilization phase.
8. Post-Implementation Support and Maintenance
● Provide a warranty period for support, bug fixes, and performance monitoring.
● Recommend and optionally offer a Service Level Agreement (SLA) for extended
technical support and maintenance.
