4 Interdepartmental Referral 1. A case (enquiry, request, or complaint) is logged
in CRM and assigned to a division (e.g. Exams).
2. The assigned officer reviews the case and
determines that another department's input or
action is required.
3. Using CRM's referral function, the officer
internally forwards the case to the relevant
division (e.g. Finance, Legal).
4. CRM notifies the receiving department/officer and
logs the handover.
5. The receiving officer opens the case and
performs their action or provides a response.
6. They update the case in CRM, adding internal
notes or resolution status.
7. The case either:
⮚ Is finalized by the second department, or
⮚ Returns to the originating officer for final
communication with the stakeholder.
8. The originating officer confirms resolution and
closes the case.
9. CRM records full referral history, timestamps,
and all actions across departments.
5 Follow-Up and Escalation 1. A case is logged and assigned to the responsible
officer, along with its SLA timer (based on the
service type).
2. CRM begins tracking time from the moment the
case is created.
No Workflow High Level Steps
3. As the SLA deadline approaches:
⮚ CRM automatically sends a reminder/alert to the
assigned officer.
⮚ The officer may take action, update progress, or
resolve the case.
4. If the officer does not act in time:
⮚ CRM auto-escalates the case to a supervisor or
designated senior staff based on escalation rules.
5. The supervisor receives a notification and opens
the case.
6. Supervisor reviews the case, internal notes, and
elapsed time.
7. The case may be:
⮚ Reassigned to a new officer.
⮚ Intervened directly by the supervisor.
⮚ Reclassified or flagged for urgent attention.
8. CRM records the escalation timestamp, reason,
and who took over.
9. Once resolved, the case is closed and marked
accordingly.
10.Escalation history is available in audit logs and
SLA compliance reports.
B Indicative CRM Functional Areas (Marketing and Communication Use Case)
The following modules and capabilities are indicative of the functionalities expected under the proposed
CRM system. Bidders are encouraged to demonstrate these in their technical proposal and demo, and
to explain how their solution supports these areas.
1. Sales Management
● Lead & Opportunity Tracking – Capture, qualify, and nurture leads.
● Pipeline Management – Visualize sales stages and forecast revenue.
● Deal & Proposal Management – Track negotiations and close deals faster.
● Automated Sales Processes – Set reminders, follow-ups, and workflows.
2. Marketing Automation
● Campaign Management – Plan, execute, and track marketing campaigns.
● Email Marketing – Send personalized bulk emails and track engagement.
● Lead Scoring – Prioritize leads based on engagement and behavior.
● Social Media Integration – Manage and track social interactions.
3. Customer Service & Support
● Ticketing System – Log, assign, and resolve customer issues.
● Knowledge Base / Self-Service – Provide FAQs and help articles.
● Live Chat & Chatbots – Offer real-time support.
● Customer Feedback & Surveys – Collect and analyze feedback.
4. Contact & Account Management
● Centralized Customer Database – Store contact details, interactions, and history.
● Segmentation – Group customers based on behaviour, demographics, etc.
Relationship Tracking – Log calls, meetings, and emails automatically.
5. Analytics & Reporting
● Dashboards & KPIs – Track sales performance, customer satisfaction, etc.
● Custom Reports – Generate insights on revenue, churn rate, and trends.
● Predictive Analytics – Forecast sales and customer behaviour.
6. Workflow & Process Automation
● Task Automation – Automate repetitive tasks (e.g., follow-up emails).
● Approval Workflows – Streamline internal processes (e.g., discounts, contracts).
● AI-Powered Insight – Suggest next best actions for sales or support.
● Upsell/Cross-sell Recommendations – Suggest related products/services.
7. Customer Retention & Loyalty Programs
● Loyalty Tracking – Reward repeat customers with points/discounts.
● Personalized Engagement – Send tailored offers and recommendations.
8. Collaboration & Team Management
● Internal Communication – Share notes and updates within teams.
● Role-Based Access – Control data visibility for different users.
● Activity Tracking – Monitor team performance and productivity.
